56
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:02,340
A suspect in police custody died.

57
00:07:02,810 --> 00:07:04,610
The serial killer, the Eraser.

58
00:07:05,210 --> 00:07:07,440
Those two phrases must be aired.

59
00:07:07,540 --> 00:07:09,980
Contact all your sources from the police department...

60
00:07:10,110 --> 00:07:12,750
and draw help from our other departments.

61
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:13,850
This must be the headline news.

62
00:07:14,150 --> 00:07:15,550
Which should we go after first?

63
00:07:15,790 --> 00:07:17,250
The Metropolitan Investigation Unit, of course.

64
00:07:17,690 --> 00:07:19,890
Make sure to add Dong Baek's name though.

65
00:07:20,060 --> 00:07:23,430
Paint a picture of how this is all because of people...

66
00:07:23,760 --> 00:07:25,430
like Dong Baek.

67
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:28,600
Sorry I'm late. Sorry.

68
00:07:30,530 --> 00:07:31,630
You!

69
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:34,540
- Yes? - Who said you could come in?

70
00:07:36,540 --> 00:07:37,640
Me?

71
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:41,840
Did she do as the director asked?

72
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,450
You're banned from the newsroom.

73
00:07:48,020 --> 00:07:49,120
But...

74
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:52,690
Everyone said that Detective Dong is done for anyway...

75
00:07:52,690 --> 00:07:55,660
- since he'll be found guilty... - So what?

76
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:58,290
Who do you think you are to make these decisions?

77
00:08:01,260 --> 00:08:02,400
I apologize, sir.

78
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:04,470
Until you find hard evidence to bring Dong Baek down,

79
00:08:04,470 --> 00:08:06,540
you are not to step foot in here again.

80
00:08:07,970 --> 00:08:09,470
Now get lost!

81
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:43,570
(Captain Koo Kyung Tan)

82
00:08:47,140 --> 00:08:50,150
